Common types[edit]
In musical terms, particularly in the fields of music history and music analysis, some common terms for different types of texture are:
Type
Description
Visual
Audio
Monophonic
Monophonic texture includes a single melodic line with no accompaniment. (Benward & Saker 2003, p. 136). PSMs often double or parallel the PM they support (Benward & Saker 2003, p. 137).
"Pop Goes the Weasel" melody (Kliewer 1975, pp. 270–301).
